OL,3,CPeople asked to avoid Welsh river over
OL,4,Cof 'crayfish plague' harmless to humans
OL,6,FPeople have been told not to go into a
OL,7,FWelsh river after a number of dead
OL,8,Fcrayfish were discovered, sparking
OL,9,Ffears of the spread a plague deadly to
OL,10,Fthe crustacean but harmless to humans.
OL,12,FNatural Resources Wales (NRW) is
OL,13,Fcarrying out urgent tests on the River
OL,14,FIrfon near Builth Wells after they
OL,15,Freceived reports of dead crayfish.
OL,17,FIt is believed the deaths may be
OL,18,Flinked to "crayfish plague", a highly
OL,19,Finfectious disease that is fatal to
OL,20,Fcrayfish but does not affect people or
OL,21,Fother wildlife.
