OL,3,CPeople asked to avoid Welsh river over
OL,4,Cof 'crayfish plague' harmless to humans
OL,6,F"The native, white-clawed crayfish is
OL,7,Fone of the reasons the River Wye has
OL,8,Fbeen designated a Special Area of
OL,9,FConservation so it's crucial that we
OL,10,Flimit the spread of the plague to
OL,11,Fprotect other local populations.
OL,13,F"By staying out of the river, we can
OL,14,Fhelp stop the spread of this disease
OL,15,Fand protect these valuable creatures."
OL,17,FShe added that the crayfish is
OL,18,F"essential for our ecosystem" and
OL,19,Findicates healthy, clean rivers.
